<dashboard version="1.1" theme="dark">
  <label>T1021.001 â€” RDP Lateral Movement</label>
  <description>Detects post-compromise lateral movement via Remote Desktop by flagging sources that touch 3+ distinct internal destinations on TCP/3389 in a 1-h window.</description>

  <fieldset submitButton="false" autoRun="true">
    <input type="time" token="time">
      <label>Time range</label>
      <default>
        <earliest>-24h@h</earliest>
        <latest>now</latest>
      </default>
    </input>
    <input type="text" token="src_filter" searchWhenChanged="true">
      <label>Source IP</label>
      <default>*</default>
    </input>
  </fieldset>

  <row>
    <panel>
      <title>Active pivots</title>
      <single>
        <search>
          <query>`rdp_lateral`
| where like(src, "$src_filter$") OR "$src_filter$"="*"
| stats count</query>
          <earliest>$time.earliest$</earliest>
          <latest>$time.latest$</latest>
        </search>
        <option name="colorBy">value</option>
        <option name="rangeValues">[0,1,3]</option>
        <option name="rangeColors">["0x53a051","0xf8be34","0xdc4e41"]</option>
        <option name="useColors">1</option>
      </single>
    </panel>
    <panel>
      <title>Distinct attacker sources</title>
      <single>
        <search>
          <query>`rdp_lateral`
| where like(src, "$src_filter$") OR "$src_filter$"="*"
| stats dc(src)</query>
          <earliest>$time.earliest$</earliest>
          <latest>$time.latest$</latest>
        </search>
      </single>
    </panel>
    <panel>
      <title>Distinct victim hosts</title>
      <single>
        <search>
          <query>index=zeek sourcetype=zeek:conn 'id.resp_p'=3389
| stats dc("id.resp_h")</query>
          <earliest>$time.earliest$</earliest>
          <latest>$time.latest$</latest>
        </search>
      </single>
    </panel>
  </row>

  <row>
    <panel>
      <title>Active pivots</title>
      <table>
        <search>
          <query>`rdp_lateral`
| where like(src, "$src_filter$") OR "$src_filter$"="*"
| eval window=strftime(_time, "%Y-%m-%d %H:%M")
| sort -distinct_destinations
| table window, src, distinct_destinations, total_connections, duration_seconds, sample_destinations</query>
          <earliest>$time.earliest$</earliest>
          <latest>$time.latest$</latest>
        </search>
        <option name="count">25</option>
      </table>
    </panel>
  </row>

  <row>
    <panel>
      <title>RDP connection rate, top sources</title>
      <chart>
        <search>
          <query>index=zeek sourcetype=zeek:conn 'id.resp_p'=3389
| where like(src, "$src_filter$") OR "$src_filter$"="*"
| timechart span=15m count BY src limit=8</query>
          <earliest>$time.earliest$</earliest>
          <latest>$time.latest$</latest>
        </search>
        <option name="charting.chart">column</option>
        <option name="charting.chart.stackMode">stacked</option>
      </chart>
    </panel>
  </row>

  <row>
    <panel>
      <title>About this detection</title>
      <html>
        <h3>T1021.001 â€” RDP Lateral Movement</h3>
        <p>
          After a foothold + credential acquisition, ransomware operators
          pivot via Remote Desktop into multiple internal Windows boxes.
          The DFIR Report has documented this as the dominant
          lateral-movement signature in 2023â€“2025 ransomware engagements.
        </p>
        <p>
          The detection groups conn.log on TCP/3389 by (1-h window, src)
          and fires when one source touches â‰Ą 3 distinct internal
          destinations. Allow-list IT admins / jump hosts in
          <code>rdp_admin_allowlist.csv</code> to suppress benign
          multi-host activity.
        </p>
        <p>
          Tuning + false-positive notes:
          <a href="https://github.com/JacobRHess/detlab/blob/main/cases/t1021_001_rdp_lateral/README.md" target="_blank">cases/t1021_001_rdp_lateral/README.md</a>
        </p>
      </html>
    </panel>
  </row>
</dashboard>
